This Netflix clone project utilizes **ReactJS** for the frontend and **Firebase** as the backend service. It also integrates with the **Movie Database API (TMDB)** to display movie details.

---

## Key Features

### User Authentication
- **Firebase Authentication** is used for user sign-up and login.
- User information is stored in the **Firestore database**.

### Homepage
- **Navigation Bar**: Includes a logo, menu links (e.g., TV Shows, Movies, New & Popular, My List), and icons for search, notifications, and user profile with a logout option.
- **Hero Section**: Features a movie banner image, text, and "Play" and "More Info" buttons.
- **Movie Lists**: Displays various categories of movies (e.g., Blockbuster, Only on Netflix, Upcoming, Top Picks) in horizontally scrollable lists.
- **Footer**: Contains social media icons and menu links.

### Video Playback
- Clicking on a movie thumbnail opens a **player page** that displays the movie trailer video.
- The player page shows the movie title, published date, and type.
- A **back icon** allows users to return to the homepage.

### Responsiveness
- The website is **fully responsive**, ensuring it looks good on smaller screens.